result.adr_address: 46號 Staunton St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: McSorley's Ale House

reviews.text: Cosy place to sit down and grab a beer and relax on a slow night, but the real value of going here is for watching football games with a highly committed crowd. If that's your thing, bump up to 5 stars! Easy to get around to multiple other restaurants as well (as long as you watch those beers) and a nice vibe so a recommendation for people who simply like a good night out either way.

Thanks for making me feel at home in Melbourne once again. The atmosphere, where a couple of guests barracked for Richmond was like being back home in Australia. Good curry and really nice selection of beer as well.
A popular Irish theme pub offering Irish beer and comfort food. Free wifi and portable charger available.

Great venue for watching the sporting screens.. good curry options in true Brit pub-stylee and the burger was delightfully immense and tasty.. air con dripping wasn't such a great feature, and the cheesey meatball starter was a little bit mean on the portion size.. but otherwise, great little perching spot for an afternoon pint.

My pilgrimage in search of good beer lead me here but to be quite frank I was really disappointed. As a Brit, the lure of an ‘ale house’ was too strong. Sadly, only gas fed beverages were on offer and of the larger variety. Boo. The stools were too high compared to the barrel style tables and I sat like a hunch back whilst sampling the ‘house ale’. Not what I signed up for. Plus some angry American at the bar started punching a taxi, it was entertaining and not entirely the bars fault, he was fairly well oiled.

result.adr_address: Discovery Bay Rd, Discovery Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: Discovery Bay Rd, Discovery Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Discovery Bay Plaza

reviews.text: Nice place with good food and places to shop, would say it needs a fresh coat of paint (but where doesn't in Hong Kong with the humidity). The ferry (runs to Central) is easy to get to and runs I think every 30 minutes. Is you get a chance to go to the Korean place where you grill your own food, you must, fantastic food.
Great place overlooking the beach and close to ferry

Major commercial centre for Discovery Bay residents. Banks, supermarket, salon, department and grocery stores intend for maximum convenience. Residents and tourists never need to worry about food as there are numerous cuisine choices: Italian, Middle East, Mexican, BBQ, Chinese, bars and pubs. Fairs are also held for festival celebrations. Unfortunately the bus terminal and part of the shopping mall is under expansion which is expected to complete in 2019. Nevertheless old needs to go for new to come!  Look forward to the new look of DB Plaza!
Nice plaza and square. Plenty of restaurants with outdoor seating and some shops as well.
Europe style. A completely different feel, very relaxed.
